cloudctl is a DevOps Toolkit for provisioning various cloud provider configuration

First time setup:
1. Create namespace file in the root cli directory.
File content example:
ORGANIZATION=cermati
TEAM=indodana
PRODUCT=midas
PROJECT_DIRECTORY=$(pwd)

2. Request cloudctl-{environment} certificate bundle (Need pkictl to be installed)
./pkictl member certs get

3. Setup cloudctl
./cloudctl setup

I. Configure AWS Dynamic credentials to Vault
1. Export the necessary variables
export GITHUB_USERNAME="YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME"
export AWS_VAULT_ACCESS_KEY="TO_BE_FILLED"
export AWS_VAULT_ACCESS_SECRET_KEY="TO_BE_FILLED"

2. Configure the Role to Vault
./cloudctl aws role configure <service> <environment> <role>